b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Crowdin and ModernMT share a solid foundation of core features including Machine Translation, Translation Memory, Api Access, Real Time. Where Crowdin pulls ahead is with exclusive access to Glossary and File Formats and Team Collaboration and Quality Assurance and Cms Integration, which can be a deciding factor for teams that rely on these capabilities. On the other hand, ModernMT uniquely offers Custom Models, giving it an edge for users who prioritize this area. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Crowdin holds an overall score of 7/10 and an ease of use score of 6/10, while ModernMT scores 7/10 overall and 7/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Crowdin offers a more budget-friendly entry point at Free, compared to ModernMT's starting price of $25/mo. Crowdin has a notable advantage here with its free plan, allowing you to get started without any financial commitment. ModernMT does not currently offer a free tier, which means you will need to pay from day one."}]]}]
